1
00:01:23,314 --> 00:01:25,747
[BELLS RINGING;
CHATTERING]

2
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:27,884
- LATER!

3
00:01:27,917 --> 00:01:29,484
- HOLD IT!
GET BACK HERE!

4
00:01:29,517 --> 00:01:31,050
YOU'RE ON CLEANING DUTY!

5
00:01:31,084 --> 00:01:33,017
- I KNOW, BUT I'VE
GOT TO MEET SOMEONE.

6
00:01:33,050 --> 00:01:35,317
I PROMISE, I'LL
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

7
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:37,984
- DON'T TELL ME--YOU'RE
GOING TO SEE YOUR BOYFRIEND.

8
00:01:38,017 --> 00:01:38,984
- SHE WOULDN'T, WOULD SHE?

9
00:01:39,017 --> 00:01:42,284
- I TOLD YOU ALREADY!
I DO NOT HAVE A BOYFRIEND!

10
00:01:42,317 --> 00:01:45,517
GOOD-BYE.
I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

11
00:01:45,550 --> 00:01:47,650
OH!

12
00:01:52,017 --> 00:01:52,750
- UH...

13
00:01:52,784 --> 00:01:54,384
- IT HITS ALL
THE PRESSURE POINTS.

14
00:01:54,417 --> 00:01:55,684
CAN'T HURT TO TRY IT.

15
00:01:55,717 --> 00:01:56,984
- UH, I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

16
00:01:57,017 --> 00:01:58,984
- GOT TO GIVE HIM POINTS
FOR BEING PERSISTENT.

17
00:01:59,017 --> 00:02:01,784
- HE MIGHT HAVE
BETTER LUCK WITH FLOWERS.

18
00:02:01,817 --> 00:02:02,684
- MM-HMM.

19
00:02:02,717 --> 00:02:04,284
- I KNOW SITTING BOTHERS YOU,

20
00:02:04,317 --> 00:02:07,317
BUT DO YOU THINK YOU COULD
MAKE IT THROUGH A MOVIE?

21
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:09,017
IT'S JUST 2 HOURS.

22
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:10,750
- UH...

23
00:02:10,784 --> 00:02:12,750
- HUDDLE!

24
00:02:12,784 --> 00:02:14,050
- WAIT A SEC.

25
00:02:14,084 --> 00:02:16,417
DID HE JUST ASK ME
ON A DATE?

26
00:02:16,450 --> 00:02:18,384
- THAT'S WHAT
IT LOOKED LIKE TO ME.

27
00:02:18,417 --> 00:02:19,217
- WHY DON'T YOU GO?

28
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:20,984
- YOU'D BE THE ENVY
OF ALL THE GIRLS,

29
00:02:21,017 --> 00:02:23,617
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING
IT'S YOUR FIRST DATE.

30
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:24,817
- UH...
- GET REAL!

31
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:27,617
YOU MEAN YOU'VE NEVER, EVER
BEEN ON A DATE BEFORE?

32
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:30,284
- COME ON!
GIVE ME A BREAK HERE!

33
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:33,217
OF COURSE I HAVE!

34
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:34,984
NOT.

35
00:02:35,017 --> 00:02:35,950
THE MOVIES, HUH?

36
00:02:35,984 --> 00:02:38,550
SURE. I GUESS
WE COULD GO TOGETHER.

37
00:02:38,584 --> 00:02:40,750
- HEY, THAT'S GREAT.
SEE YOU SATURDAY.

38
00:02:40,784 --> 00:02:43,417
I'LL SWING BY YOUR PLACE
AT HALF PAST 6:00.

39
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,050
- HUH?
HALF PAST!

40
00:02:45,084 --> 00:02:47,184
OH, NO!
THE PAST IS THE PROBLEM!

41
00:02:47,217 --> 00:02:48,917
WHAT IF I DON'T
GET BACK IN TIME?

42
00:02:48,950 --> 00:02:51,584
I'LL MISS MY VERY FIRST DATE!

43
00:02:51,850 --> 00:02:53,984
INUYASHA, WHAT DO YOU
THINK THE CHANCES ARE

44
00:02:54,017 --> 00:02:55,384
OF GETTING BACK
BY SATURDAY?

45
00:02:55,417 --> 00:02:57,817
- UH, FAIR TO MODERATE,
IF WE'RE LUCKY.

46
00:02:57,850 --> 00:02:58,984
- OH, GREAT.

47
00:02:59,017 --> 00:03:02,784
- WHEN EXACTLY WAS THIS
SATURDAY OF YOURS AGAIN?

48
00:03:02,817 --> 00:03:05,184
- OH...I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.

49
00:03:05,217 --> 00:03:07,150
- HMM!

50
00:03:13,284 --> 00:03:15,950
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

51
00:03:15,984 --> 00:03:19,150
- WOW!
THIS IS AWESOME!

52
00:03:19,184 --> 00:03:20,184
LOOK! A FISH!

53
00:03:20,217 --> 00:03:21,650
- YOU MIND FOCUSING A LITTLE?

54
00:03:21,684 --> 00:03:23,784
WE'RE NOT HERE
TO LOOK AT THE SCENERY.

55
00:03:23,817 --> 00:03:25,484
- AYE-AYE, MON CAPITAN.

56
00:03:25,517 --> 00:03:28,450
ON THE LOOKOUT FOR SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL!

57
00:03:28,484 --> 00:03:29,717
[GROANING]

58
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,450
- SHIPPO, YOU CALL
YOURSELF A DEMON?

59
00:03:32,484 --> 00:03:34,350
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO GET SEASICK.

60
00:03:34,384 --> 00:03:35,717
- I'M NOT TRYING.

61
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:36,517
- THIS IS PATHETIC.

62
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,017
- WE'RE NOT GOING
TO FIND ANY SHARDS

63
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:39,817
UNLESS YOU TWO SNAP TO IT.

64
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:41,817
HMM?
- WHAT IS IT?

65
00:03:41,850 --> 00:03:43,850
- SPIDERWEBS.

66
00:03:43,884 --> 00:03:47,484
- THOSE ARE SPIDERWEBS?
ARE YOU SURE?

67
00:03:51,017 --> 00:03:53,384
- HUH. HMM.

68
00:03:53,417 --> 00:03:56,317
- MASTER INUYASHA,
WHAT MANNER OF WEBS ARE THEY?

69
00:03:56,350 --> 00:03:58,284
- NOTHING TO BE
CONCERNED ABOUT.

70
00:03:58,317 --> 00:03:59,750
HUH?
- UP THERE!

71
00:03:59,784 --> 00:04:01,117
- KEEP AWAY FROM ME!

72
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:03,917
AAH!

73
00:04:05,917 --> 00:04:08,317
- GOOD CATCH, INUYASHA!

74
00:04:08,884 --> 00:04:10,750
- LOOKS LIKE
SOME TYPE OF DEMON.

75
00:04:10,784 --> 00:04:13,984
- MY THANKS. YOU SAVED ME
FROM CERTAIN DEATH.

76
00:04:14,017 --> 00:04:15,950
OH!
- HUH?

77
00:04:15,984 --> 00:04:17,750
- DEMON! UNHAND ME!

78
00:04:17,784 --> 00:04:20,317
- AAH!
- AAH!

79
00:04:21,217 --> 00:04:24,617
- THINK OF THIS AS PRESERVED
HERBS FOR AILMENTS.

80
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:25,684
[GRUMBLING]

81
00:04:25,717 --> 00:04:28,650
- DO YOU MIND MY ASKING
WHAT WAS AFTER YOU JUST NOW?

82
00:04:28,684 --> 00:04:30,817
- A DEMON KNOWN AS
A SPIDER HEAD.

83
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:31,884
THESE MOUNTAINS
HAVE BEEN PLAGUED

84
00:04:31,917 --> 00:04:33,984
BY THEIR EVIL PRESENCE
SINCE SPRINGTIME.

85
00:04:34,017 --> 00:04:37,317
SEVERAL VILLAGES HAVE
ALREADY BEEN ATTACKED.

86
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,284
SPIDER HEADS TRAP HUMANS
IN THEIR WEBS,

87
00:04:39,317 --> 00:04:41,417
PARALYZE THEM,
AND DEVOUR THEM ALIVE.

88
00:04:41,450 --> 00:04:42,950
THEY ARE TERRIFYING DEMONS.

89
00:04:42,984 --> 00:04:44,017
- YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN.

90
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:47,184
- HEY, INUYASHA, WE HAVE
TO DO SOMETHING TO HELP.

91
00:04:47,217 --> 00:04:49,217
- ANY SIGN OF THE SACRED
JEWEL FRAGMENTS?

92
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:51,084
- NOT YET, AND I DIDN'T
PICK UP ANYTHING

93
00:04:51,117 --> 00:04:52,784
FROM THE SPIDER HEAD
JUST NOW.

94
00:04:52,817 --> 00:04:53,817
- THEN LET'S MOVE OUT.

95
00:04:53,850 --> 00:04:56,484
I WANT TO CROSS THESE
MOUNTAINS BEFORE NIGHTFALL.

96
00:04:56,517 --> 00:04:58,284
- WE CAN'T JUST WALK AWAY!

97
00:04:58,317 --> 00:04:59,550
THERE'S A DEMON ON THE LOOSE!

98
00:04:59,584 --> 00:05:02,150
- LISTEN, I DON'T GO
SLAYING DEMONS

99
00:05:02,184 --> 00:05:04,717
EVERY TIME A HUMAN COMES
RUNNING SCARED TO ME.

100
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,484
- NO ONE'S SUGGESTING YOU DO.

101
00:05:06,517 --> 00:05:07,884
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO HIM?

102
00:05:07,917 --> 00:05:10,117
USUALLY, HE'D AT LEAST
CHECK THINGS OUT.

103
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:11,150
- I'M LEAVING.

104
00:05:11,184 --> 00:05:13,817
BEING OBLIGED TO A DEMON
DOES NOT SIT WELL WITH ME.

105
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:15,450
- FEIGNING SOME MEASURE
OF GRATITUDE

106
00:05:15,484 --> 00:05:17,417
MIGHT SIT BETTER
WITH US, THOUGH.

107
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:19,250
- INSOLENT BEAST!

108
00:05:19,284 --> 00:05:23,417
THANK YOU FOR REMINDING ME
WHY I DETEST DEMONS.

109
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:25,384
[GRUNTING]

110
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:28,417
AAH!

111
00:05:28,450 --> 00:05:29,817
[THUD]

112
00:05:29,850 --> 00:05:33,617
- HOW ABOUT DISPLAYING SOME
OF THAT OLD-FASHIONED CHIVALRY?

113
00:05:33,650 --> 00:05:36,517
THAT MUST BE THE TEMPLE.

114
00:05:36,550 --> 00:05:39,250
SEE? THAT WASN'T
SO BAD, WAS IT?

115
00:05:39,284 --> 00:05:41,250
- HMM!

116
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:48,650
- YOU HAVE RETURNED.
ARE YOU INJURED, NAZUNA?

117
00:05:48,684 --> 00:05:50,417
- OH, MASTER!

118
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:55,784
- OH, I FEARED THAT A SPIDER
HEAD MAY HAVE ATTACKED YOU.

119
00:05:55,817 --> 00:05:58,017
- IT SPIED ME WHILE I ATTENDED
TO THE GRAVE SITES.

120
00:05:58,050 --> 00:06:02,217
I HAD NO CHOICE BUT TO RELY ON
THESE DEMONS TO BRING ME HOME.

121
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,317
I'M SORRY, MASTER.

122
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:06,417
- ALL DEMONS ARE NOT
CREATED EQUAL, YOU KNOW.

123
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,550
- I DON'T SUPPOSE THEY ARE.

124
00:06:08,584 --> 00:06:11,484
- OH, MAN. DON'T WORRY.
WE'RE LEAVING ANYWAY.

125
00:06:11,517 --> 00:06:15,684
- WAIT, FRIENDS!
YOU MUST STAY THE NIGHT
HERE WITH US AT THE TEMPLE.

126
00:06:15,717 --> 00:06:16,684
- NO, MASTER!

127
00:06:16,717 --> 00:06:21,184
- GO. PREPARE A MEAL
FOR YOUR KIND GUESTS.

128
00:06:21,217 --> 00:06:22,650
- YES.

129
00:06:22,684 --> 00:06:25,450
- I BEG YOU DO FORGIVE
NAZUNA FOR HER RUDENESS.

130
00:06:25,484 --> 00:06:27,784
HER PARENTS WERE
KILLED BY A SPIDER HEAD,

131
00:06:27,817 --> 00:06:30,450
AND SHE HAS HARBORED
AN UNDERSTANDABLE FEAR

132
00:06:30,484 --> 00:06:32,317
OF DEMONS SINCE THE INCIDENT.

133
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:35,850
I HAVE ATTEMPTED TO QUELL
HER FEARS BUT TO NO AVAIL.

134
00:06:35,884 --> 00:06:38,617
- SO, WE PROBABLY WON'T RUN INTO
ONE OF THOSE SPIDER HEADS

135
00:06:38,650 --> 00:06:40,250
ON OUR WAY THROUGH
THE MOUNTAINS, WILL WE?

136
00:06:40,284 --> 00:06:43,684
- AS THE NUMBER OF MEN
DYING IN WARS INCREASES,

137
00:06:43,717 --> 00:06:46,117
SO DO THE NUMBER
OF SPIDER HEADS...

138
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:48,184
BY LEAPS AND BOUNDS.

139
00:06:48,217 --> 00:06:49,117
- LEAPS AND...

140
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:51,150
SAY, HOW ABOUT WE
TAKE HIM UP ON HIS OFFER?

141
00:06:51,184 --> 00:06:53,650
- UH, WE'RE ON A QUEST,
AND I REFUSE TO ALLOW

142
00:06:53,684 --> 00:06:55,850
SOME MEASLY SPIDERS
TO STOP US.

143
00:06:55,884 --> 00:06:58,884
- STAY THE NIGHT WITH US
AND REST WITH EASE.

144
00:06:58,917 --> 00:07:01,517
I HAVE POSTED SUTRAS
THROUGHOUT THE TEMPLE

145
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:04,317
TO WARD OFF ANY DEMONS
FROM ATTACKING US.

146
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:06,117
- UH...WHAT DO YOU SAY?

147
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:09,050
- SUPPOSE THERE'S
NO SENSE ARGUING.

148
00:07:09,084 --> 00:07:10,884
[GIGGLES]

149
00:07:13,517 --> 00:07:15,150
- AHH! WHAT A DELICIOUS MEAL.

150
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:17,884
PERHAPS WE SHOULD STAY
A FEW DAYS AND GET
TO KNOW NAZUNA BETTER.

151
00:07:17,917 --> 00:07:22,017
- FUNNY HOW A COUPLE
BOWLS OF RICE CAN CHANGE
YOUR TUNE ABOUT SOMEONE.

152
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:23,050
- I LIKED HER FROM THE START.

153
00:07:23,084 --> 00:07:25,817
I MERELY THOUGHT
SHE WAS LACKING IN MANNERS.

154
00:07:25,850 --> 00:07:28,650
- IT'S GETTING LATE.

155
00:07:28,684 --> 00:07:30,317
- HEY, INUYASHA?

156
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:31,384
- HMM?

157
00:07:31,417 --> 00:07:32,984
- WHY THE LONG FACE?

158
00:07:33,017 --> 00:07:36,050
- HMMPH. IT'S NOTHING.

159
00:07:36,084 --> 00:07:37,417
WHAT?
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM?

160
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:41,217
- WAIT A SECOND.
I KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

161
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,450
- HMM?

162
00:07:42,484 --> 00:07:44,450
- YOU'RE AFRAID OF SPIDERS!

163
00:07:44,484 --> 00:07:48,317
- WHOA! WHO'S AFRAID
OF THE BIG, BAD SPIDER?

164
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:49,284
OH!

165
00:07:49,317 --> 00:07:50,384
- I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

166
00:07:50,417 --> 00:07:51,750
- I'M NOT AFRAID OF SPIDERS!

167
00:07:51,784 --> 00:07:53,584
- NOW WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

168
00:07:53,617 --> 00:07:55,384
- TO GET SOME FRESH AIR!

169
00:07:55,417 --> 00:07:58,284
I'M SLEEPING
OUTSIDE TONIGHT.

170
00:07:58,317 --> 00:07:59,150
HUH?

171
00:07:59,184 --> 00:08:01,117
DAMN! WE'RE SURROUNDED.

172
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:03,884
HOW COULD I HAVE MISSED
THEIR SCENT?

173
00:08:05,584 --> 00:08:08,284
- AAH! SPIDER HEADS!

174
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,384
AAH!
- LOOK OUT!

175
00:08:11,417 --> 00:08:12,684
THEY'RE BEHIND US, TOO!

176
00:08:12,717 --> 00:08:13,617
- THEIR NUMBERS ARE GREAT,

177
00:08:13,650 --> 00:08:15,750
BUT THEY ARE NOT
A FORMIDABLE ENEMY.

178
00:08:15,784 --> 00:08:18,850
UP FOR SOME AFTER-DINNER
EXERCISE, MASTER?

179
00:08:18,884 --> 00:08:20,017
- OH, YEAH.

180
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:21,217
WARD THEM OFF.

181
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,784
SO MUCH FOR
THE OLD PRIEST'S SUTRAS.

182
00:08:23,817 --> 00:08:25,150
- MASTER!

183
00:08:25,184 --> 00:08:27,284
MASTER!
THE SPIDER HEADS! OH!

184
00:08:27,317 --> 00:08:29,417
THEY'VE GOT YOU!

185
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:31,417
- AAH!

186
00:08:39,517 --> 00:08:41,484
- INUYASHA!
- MAKE A BREAK!

187
00:08:41,517 --> 00:08:42,984
I'LL BE RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

188
00:08:43,017 --> 00:08:44,784
- BUT WE CAN'T--
- DO WHAT I SAY!

189
00:08:44,817 --> 00:08:46,450
I CAN HANDLE THESE DEMONS.
HYAH!

190
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:48,550
- WHY'S HE ACTING
SO STRANGE TODAY?

191
00:08:48,584 --> 00:08:52,184
- AND WHY ISN'T
THE TETSUSAIGA TRANSFORMING?

192
00:08:52,984 --> 00:08:55,550
- AAH! AAH!

193
00:08:57,817 --> 00:09:00,184
- FOX FIRE!

194
00:09:01,784 --> 00:09:03,317
- I'VE GOT YOU!

195
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,150
- WE'VE GOT TO ESCAPE!

196
00:09:05,184 --> 00:09:09,050
- NAZUNA! THE DEMONS HAVE
BROKEN THROUGH MY SEALS.

197
00:09:09,084 --> 00:09:11,584
MY SUTRAS ARE
NO LONGER STRONG ENOUGH

198
00:09:11,617 --> 00:09:14,184
TO WARD OFF THE SPIDER HEADS.

199
00:09:14,217 --> 00:09:16,517
- OH, MASTER!

200
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:19,450
MASTER, NO!

201
00:09:19,484 --> 00:09:21,417
[PANTING]

202
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:23,484
- WE SHOULD BE SAFE HERE.

203
00:09:23,517 --> 00:09:26,417
[SIGHS]

204
00:09:26,450 --> 00:09:27,484
- DAMN IT.

205
00:09:27,517 --> 00:09:28,550
- WHAT'S WITH YOU?

206
00:09:28,584 --> 00:09:29,984
YOU'RE ACTING
WEIRDER THAN NORMAL.

207
00:09:30,017 --> 00:09:31,217
- LEAVE ME ALONE!
[KAGOME GASPS]

208
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:34,050
- WHAT HAS GOTTEN INTO YOU?

209
00:09:34,084 --> 00:09:34,817
HUH?

210
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:36,817
- FORGET ABOUT ME FOR NOW.

211
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:38,984
YOU SHOULD BE MORE WORRIED
ABOUT YOURSELVES.

212
00:09:39,017 --> 00:09:40,984
- YOUR HAIR'S GONE BLACK.

213
00:09:41,017 --> 00:09:42,084
[SIGHS]

214
00:09:42,117 --> 00:09:43,917
- IF YOU THINK YOU CAN
RELY ON MY STRENGTH

215
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:47,284
TO SAVE YOU THIS TIME,
YOU'D BETTER THINK AGAIN.

216
00:09:47,317 --> 00:09:48,350
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

217
00:09:48,384 --> 00:09:50,450
- INUYASHA?
IS THAT YOU?

218
00:09:50,484 --> 00:09:52,617
- NO. I'M A TALKING PUPPET.

219
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:53,550
- UGH!

220
00:09:53,584 --> 00:09:54,517
HIS DOG EARS ARE GONE.

221
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,684
- YOU'RE NOT HALF DEMON ANYMORE.
YOU'RE HUMAN!

222
00:09:56,717 --> 00:09:59,317
- YOU'RE LUCKY MY FANGS
AND CLAWS ARE GONE.

223
00:09:59,350 --> 00:10:02,117
- ALL RIGHT. HOW ABOUT
TELLING US WHAT'S GOING ON?

224
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:05,150
- ALL HALF-DEMONS,
SUCH AS MASTER INUYASHA,

225
00:10:05,184 --> 00:10:07,250
ARE SUBJECT TO CERTAIN
TIMES WHEN THEY LOSE

226
00:10:07,284 --> 00:10:09,984
THEIR SUPERNATURAL
POWERS AS DEMONS.

227
00:10:10,017 --> 00:10:11,117
- I DON'T REALLY FOLLOW YOU.

228
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:14,217
- FROM TIME TO TIME, HALF-DEMONS
ARE RENDERED NO STRONGER

229
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,650
THAN YOURSELF
OR ANY OTHER MERE MORTAL.

230
00:10:16,684 --> 00:10:17,617
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

231
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:20,284
FOR HIM, THE TIME MUST FALL
ON THE FIRST NIGHT

232
00:10:20,317 --> 00:10:24,517
OF THE NEW CYCLE,
WHEN THE MOON IS DARK.

233
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:27,084
- OK. NOW I GET IT.

234
00:10:27,117 --> 00:10:28,584
YOU MEAN, AT THE START
OF EACH MONTH

235
00:10:28,617 --> 00:10:32,950
WHEN THE MOON ISN'T VISIBLE,
A NIGHT SUCH AS TONIGHT.

236
00:10:32,984 --> 00:10:35,517
- PRECISELY.

237
00:10:36,817 --> 00:10:39,084
- WHY, MASTER?
WHY DID YOU NOT INFORM US

238
00:10:39,117 --> 00:10:41,217
THAT YOUR PERIOD OF
VULNERABILITY WAS IMPENDING?

239
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:45,650
- BECAUSE IF I HAD, YOU WOULD
HAVE TAKEN OFF A LONG TIME AGO.

240
00:10:45,684 --> 00:10:48,250
- UH...OH?

241
00:10:48,284 --> 00:10:51,117
HMM. HAVE YOU NOT
A WHIT OF TRUST IN ME?

242
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:53,850
- YEAH, I TRUST YOU TO RUN AWAY
WHEN THERE'S TROUBLE!

243
00:10:53,884 --> 00:10:56,350
- THEN WHAT?
YOU CAN'T RELY ON ME, EITHER?

244
00:10:56,384 --> 00:10:58,217
IF YOU TOLD ME THAT YOU'D
BE LOSING YOUR POWERS,

245
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:01,384
I NEVER WOULD HAVE
INSISTED THAT WE STAY
IN THE TEMPLE WITH NAZUNA!

246
00:11:01,417 --> 00:11:04,284
SO MUCH FOR BEING ABLE
TO LEAN ON YOUR CLOSE FRIENDS!

247
00:11:04,317 --> 00:11:07,384
- I DON'T TRUST
ANYBODY, GOT IT?

248
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:08,317
[GASPS]

249
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:11,050
- HUH. IT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU.

250
00:11:11,084 --> 00:11:12,950
IT'S JUST THE WAY
I'VE LIVED UNTIL NOW.

251
00:11:12,984 --> 00:11:15,050
IT'S THE ONLY WAY I KNOW
HOW TO PROTECT MYSELF.

252
00:11:15,084 --> 00:11:16,850
- INUYASHA, I HEAR
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

253
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:21,350
I JUST WISH YOU'D OPEN UP
TO ME MORE, AS YOUR FRIEND.

254
00:11:21,384 --> 00:11:22,350
[SOBBING]
- HUH?

255
00:11:22,384 --> 00:11:25,384
NO, WAIT. I'M THE ONE
WHO'S SUPPOSED TO BE DOWN.

256
00:11:25,417 --> 00:11:28,517
- IF IT WEREN'T FOR YOUR PRIDE,
WE WOULDN'T BE IN THIS BOAT.

257
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:31,184
YOU'RE GOING TO PAY
FOR THIS BIG TIME, PAL!

258
00:11:31,217 --> 00:11:34,284
GRAB A BRAIN, WOULD YOU?
YOU DOUGH HEAD!

259
00:11:34,317 --> 00:11:35,417
- YOU'RE THE DOUGH HEAD!

260
00:11:35,450 --> 00:11:37,984
- YOU COULD HAVE SAID NO
TO STAYING AT THE TEMPLE!

261
00:11:38,017 --> 00:11:41,884
- NOW THAT INUYASHA'S BEEN
RENDERED A MERE MORTAL,

262
00:11:41,917 --> 00:11:43,984
I SHALL HAVE TO TAKE OVER
PROTECTING THE OTHERS.

263
00:11:44,017 --> 00:11:46,717
I'LL HAVE TO SUMMON
ALL MY COURAGE.

264
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:50,817
[RUSTLING LEAVES]
AAH!

265
00:11:51,550 --> 00:11:52,617
SOMEONE SAVE ME!

266
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:55,150
- NAZUNA!
- I KNEW THAT.

267
00:11:55,184 --> 00:11:56,717
- YOU MADE IT OUT OF THERE.

268
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:58,450
[PANTING]

269
00:11:58,484 --> 00:12:01,450
- PLEASE, YOU MUST RETURN
AND AID THE PRIEST.

270
00:12:01,484 --> 00:12:02,950
- WHAT?
YOU WANT US TO GO BACK?

271
00:12:02,984 --> 00:12:06,984
- YOUR DEMON IS STRONG.
I'M CERTAIN HE CAN ASSIST US.

272
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:07,684
- HUH.

273
00:12:07,717 --> 00:12:08,917
NOW, WHAT WERE YOU
SAYING ABOUT

274
00:12:08,950 --> 00:12:10,150
NOT WANTING TO BE
OBLIGED TO DEMONS?

275
00:12:10,184 --> 00:12:12,717
GET THE PRIEST TO WRITE UP
SOME MORE OF THOSE SUTRAS.

276
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,717
- YOUR COUNTENANCE
SEEMED ALTERED.

277
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:15,750
HAS YOUR HAIR NOT CHANGED?

278
00:12:15,784 --> 00:12:19,250
- HUH. IT ISN'T EASY
BEING HUMAN. BELIEVE ME.

279
00:12:19,284 --> 00:12:20,750
- AAH!
- OH, NO!

280
00:12:20,784 --> 00:12:21,850
WHAT IS IT NOW?

281
00:12:21,884 --> 00:12:23,417
- MY BAG! I FORGOT IT!

282
00:12:23,450 --> 00:12:25,484
- SO GET A NEW ONE
WHEN YOU GO BACK.

283
00:12:25,517 --> 00:12:28,484
- THING IS...
THE JEWEL SHARDS ARE INSIDE.

284
00:12:28,517 --> 00:12:30,050
- WHAT?!

285
00:12:30,084 --> 00:12:32,150
- UH...I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

286
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:33,684
- TAKE THIS.

287
00:12:33,717 --> 00:12:36,084
- YOU AND NAZUNA STAY HERE
AND DON'T THINK ABOUT MOVING.

288
00:12:36,117 --> 00:12:38,484
THE TETSUSAIGA WON'T
TRANSFORM FOR ME TONIGHT,

289
00:12:38,517 --> 00:12:42,117
BUT I'LL BE ABLE TO HANDLE A FEW
SPIDER HEADS ON MY OWN STRENGTH.

290
00:12:42,150 --> 00:12:43,317
- YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

291
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:45,884
- IT'S TIME TO GO BACK
TO THE TEMPLE, SHIPPO.

292
00:12:45,917 --> 00:12:47,484
LET'S MOVE.
- UH...

293
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:49,984
WHY DO YOU NEED ME?

294
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:51,950
[GRUNTING]

295
00:12:51,984 --> 00:12:54,517
I AM STRONG ENOUGH
TO HANDLE THIS.

296
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:55,750
[GRUNTING]

297
00:12:55,784 --> 00:12:58,250
I HAVE GOT TO BE STRONG.

298
00:13:01,784 --> 00:13:03,917
[CHUCKLING]

299
00:13:06,084 --> 00:13:08,617
- AAH! AAH!

300
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:10,050
[SHATTERING]

301
00:13:10,084 --> 00:13:11,084
- HANDS OFF!

302
00:13:11,117 --> 00:13:15,384
SO, YOU WERE PLANNING THIS
RIGHT FROM THE START.

303
00:13:15,417 --> 00:13:16,350
[CHUCKLING]

304
00:13:16,384 --> 00:13:19,017
- I COULD HARDLY CONTAIN
MYSELF WHEN I SAW YOU,

305
00:13:19,050 --> 00:13:22,517
THE HALF-DEMON RUMORED
TO POSSESS JEWEL SHARDS!

306
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:25,117
[GRUNTING]

307
00:13:28,717 --> 00:13:32,250
- THE JEWEL SHARDS!
HE SWALLOWED SOME OF THEM!

308
00:13:35,584 --> 00:13:36,884
- WHAT AN UNFORTUNATE MISHAP

309
00:13:36,917 --> 00:13:39,184
THAT YOUR SUPERHUMAN POWERS
HAVE DESERTED YOU.

310
00:13:39,217 --> 00:13:43,617
BY THE TIME I TIE THE FINAL KNOT
ON MY GAUZY WEB OF DECEIT--

311
00:13:43,650 --> 00:13:46,517
- I MAY NOT HAVE
MY USUAL POWERS...

312
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:48,584
[GRUNTING]

313
00:13:48,617 --> 00:13:50,884
BUT I'LL STILL CRUSH YOU!

314
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:54,450
- FOX FIRE!

315
00:13:54,484 --> 00:13:56,384
OH!

316
00:13:56,417 --> 00:14:01,417
- FINALLY THIS TIRESOME CHARADE
AS A HUMAN HAS ENDED!

317
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:05,850
[COWERING]

318
00:14:09,217 --> 00:14:11,450
AAH!

319
00:14:12,817 --> 00:14:14,850
[MOANING]

320
00:14:14,884 --> 00:14:16,850
- AAH!

321
00:14:16,884 --> 00:14:17,884
- INUYASHA!

322
00:14:17,917 --> 00:14:19,317
- NOW TELL ME
WHERE YOU HAVE HIDDEN

323
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:22,284
THE REMAINING SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL!

324
00:14:22,317 --> 00:14:23,684
- OVER THERE!

325
00:14:23,717 --> 00:14:26,384
- I BELIEVE YOU POSSESS THEM.

326
00:14:26,417 --> 00:14:27,517
- MASTER!

327
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:29,650
I--I DON'T UNDERSTAND!

328
00:14:29,684 --> 00:14:30,950
- HE WAS DECEIVING YOU.

329
00:14:30,984 --> 00:14:34,450
- KAGOME!
INUYASHA'S BEEN POISONED.

330
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:37,817
- HOLD ON! I'M COMING!

331
00:14:40,617 --> 00:14:41,650
- HUH?

332
00:14:41,684 --> 00:14:43,784
- THE TETSUSAIGA IS PROTECTING
YOU AS IT DID BEFORE.

333
00:14:43,817 --> 00:14:45,584
- SEEING YOU HERE
MUST MEAN WE HAVE

334
00:14:45,617 --> 00:14:47,450
A GOOD CHANCE
AT WINNING THIS BATTLE.

335
00:14:47,484 --> 00:14:48,784
OTHERWISE, YOU'D BE LONG GONE.

336
00:14:48,817 --> 00:14:51,484
- I'M NOT CERTAIN
I APPROVE OF THE INSINUATION.

337
00:14:51,517 --> 00:14:52,550
[CHUCKLES]

338
00:14:52,584 --> 00:14:54,850
- I HAVE INJECTED A LARGE
QUANTITY OF POISON IN HIM.

339
00:14:54,884 --> 00:14:58,217
HIS INNARDS WILL ALREADY
BE STARTING TO LIQUEFY.

340
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:01,917
- MASTER!
HOW CAN YOU DO THIS?

341
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:05,017
- KAGOME...SAVE YOURSELF.

342
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:07,450
- NO CHANCE.
- I'M SERIOUS.

343
00:15:07,484 --> 00:15:08,417
IT'S TOO LATE FOR ME.

344
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:10,750
- I'M NOT LEAVING HERE
WITHOUT YOU.

345
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:12,650
NO...WAY!

346
00:15:12,684 --> 00:15:14,784
[GRUNTS]

347
00:15:14,817 --> 00:15:16,350
- HUH?

348
00:15:22,384 --> 00:15:23,684
UGH!

349
00:15:23,717 --> 00:15:25,317
- WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

350
00:15:25,350 --> 00:15:26,817
- THERE'S GOT TO BE
ANOTHER WAY.

351
00:15:26,850 --> 00:15:29,217
- THERE IS A SMALL ROOM
AT THE END OF THE HALL.

352
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:32,017
QUICKLY!
- YOU CANNOT FLEE!

353
00:15:32,050 --> 00:15:34,250
[GRUNTING]

354
00:15:35,717 --> 00:15:39,417
- KAGOME, THRUST
THE TETSUSAIGA INTO THE DOOR.

355
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:41,784
QUICKLY!

356
00:15:42,384 --> 00:15:43,817
- AAH! YOU WRETCHES!

357
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:46,184
- THE TETSUSAIGA
SHOULD BE POWERFUL ENOUGH

358
00:15:46,217 --> 00:15:48,850
TO WARD THEM OFF
FOR SOME TIME.

359
00:15:48,884 --> 00:15:50,617
- HE'S FREEZING!

360
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:52,917
INUYASHA, YOU HAVE
TO STAY WITH US!

361
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:56,717
SAY SOMETHING!
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

362
00:16:07,278 --> 00:16:09,611
- THIS ALL HAPPENED,
BECAUSE I SUGGESTED

363
00:16:09,645 --> 00:16:11,078
WE STAY HERE AT THE TEMPLE.

364
00:16:11,111 --> 00:16:13,211
- YOU MUSTN'T PUT
THE BLAME ON YOURSELF.

365
00:16:13,245 --> 00:16:16,278
- BUT IT IS ALL MY FAULT!

366
00:16:18,945 --> 00:16:21,711
- I SHALL DRAW
THE POISON FROM HIS BLOOD.

367
00:16:21,745 --> 00:16:23,911
[SUCKING]

368
00:16:25,945 --> 00:16:27,878
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
I'M MYOGA.

369
00:16:27,911 --> 00:16:29,745
ALWAYS A BEAST,
NEVER A BURDEN.

370
00:16:29,778 --> 00:16:31,778
OH...
[INUYASHA MOANS]

371
00:16:31,811 --> 00:16:34,111
MASTER INUYASHA'S
SURVIVAL WILL DEPEND ON

372
00:16:34,145 --> 00:16:35,845
HIS OWN STRENGTH
FROM THIS POINT.

373
00:16:35,878 --> 00:16:36,645
[BURPS]

374
00:16:36,678 --> 00:16:39,145
[LABORED BREATHING]

375
00:16:39,778 --> 00:16:43,211
- HE'S DRIPPING IN SWEAT.

376
00:16:44,778 --> 00:16:45,811
OH.

377
00:16:45,845 --> 00:16:47,511
[MOANING]

378
00:16:47,545 --> 00:16:48,445
- HUH?
- SORRY.

379
00:16:48,478 --> 00:16:50,278
I DIDN'T
WAKE YOU UP, DID I?

380
00:16:50,311 --> 00:16:52,111
- NO.

381
00:16:52,145 --> 00:16:54,945
KAGOME.
- WHAT IS IT?

382
00:16:54,978 --> 00:16:57,378
- TELL ME SOMETHING.

383
00:16:57,411 --> 00:16:59,145
WHY WERE YOU CRYING?

384
00:16:59,178 --> 00:17:00,611
- UH...

385
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:03,378
BACK IN THE OTHER ROOM?

386
00:17:06,611 --> 00:17:09,945
BECAUSE...I THOUGHT
I WAS GOING TO LOSE YOU.

387
00:17:09,978 --> 00:17:12,511
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GOING TO...DIE.

388
00:17:12,545 --> 00:17:16,411
- YOU SHED TEARS FOR ME...

389
00:17:16,445 --> 00:17:18,311
CRIED FOR ME.

390
00:17:18,345 --> 00:17:21,445
KAGOME, IF IT'S NOT
TOO MUCH TROUBLE,

391
00:17:21,478 --> 00:17:24,011
MAY I LIE ON YOUR LAP?

392
00:17:24,045 --> 00:17:26,311
- HUH?

393
00:17:26,345 --> 00:17:27,711
MMM.

394
00:17:27,745 --> 00:17:29,311
[SIGHING]

395
00:17:39,078 --> 00:17:42,945
HOW DO YOU FEEL?
A LITTLE BETTER THAN BEFORE?

396
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:43,811
- YES.

397
00:17:43,845 --> 00:17:47,611
KAGOME...YOU SMELL
KIND OF NICE.

398
00:17:47,645 --> 00:17:48,978
- HUH?

399
00:17:49,011 --> 00:17:49,945
OK, THAT'S IT.

400
00:17:49,978 --> 00:17:51,678
YOU MADE A POINT
OF TELLING ME BEFORE

401
00:17:51,711 --> 00:17:53,611
THAT YOU COULDN'T
STAND MY SCENT.

402
00:17:53,645 --> 00:17:57,145
- I DID...BUT I WAS LYING.

403
00:17:57,178 --> 00:18:01,411
- MAYBE THIS POISON
REALLY HAS GONE TO HIS HEAD.

404
00:18:01,445 --> 00:18:04,745
YET...ALL THIS TALK
HAS MY HEART POUNDING.

405
00:18:04,778 --> 00:18:06,745
OK, NOW I'M CONFUSED.

406
00:18:06,778 --> 00:18:09,245
[SNORES]

407
00:18:09,278 --> 00:18:10,645
HE'S ASLEEP.

408
00:18:10,678 --> 00:18:13,411
[RATTLING]
WHAT?

409
00:18:13,445 --> 00:18:14,845
- AAH!
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

410
00:18:14,878 --> 00:18:16,678
- THE PRIEST MUST BE
IN PURSUIT AGAIN.

411
00:18:16,711 --> 00:18:17,645
GET THE MASTER OUT OF HERE!

412
00:18:17,678 --> 00:18:20,611
- WE'LL HAVE TO CARRY HIM.
HE'S UNCONSCIOUS.

413
00:18:20,645 --> 00:18:23,078
- AAH!

414
00:18:25,311 --> 00:18:27,245
[GROWLS]

415
00:18:29,478 --> 00:18:31,278
[SCREAMING]

416
00:18:32,578 --> 00:18:34,445
- WHOA!
- SHIPPO!

417
00:18:34,478 --> 00:18:38,211
- I MUST POSSESS
THE REMAINING JEWEL FRAGMENTS!

418
00:18:38,245 --> 00:18:41,445
- WHOA!

419
00:18:41,478 --> 00:18:43,845
[SWALLOWING]

420
00:18:43,878 --> 00:18:45,345
[GRUNTS]

421
00:18:45,378 --> 00:18:47,211
[GRIMACES]

422
00:18:47,245 --> 00:18:49,078
[LAUGHS]

423
00:18:49,111 --> 00:18:52,311
- HOW DARE YOU POSSESS
THE BODY OF MY DEAR MASTER!

424
00:18:52,345 --> 00:18:54,945
- THERE NEVER
WAS ANY PRIEST HERE.

425
00:18:54,978 --> 00:18:55,878
IT WAS ALL A TRAP

426
00:18:55,911 --> 00:18:58,745
TO LURE THE HALF-DEMON
AND HIS JEWELS TO ME!

427
00:18:58,778 --> 00:19:01,245
- YOU--YOU
SLAUGHTERED MY PARENTS

428
00:19:01,278 --> 00:19:03,478
AND ALL THE OTHER VILLAGERS?

429
00:19:03,511 --> 00:19:05,111
[LAUGHS]

430
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:08,278
- YOU SERVED ME WELL,
GULLIBLE FOOL!

431
00:19:08,311 --> 00:19:11,578
- TREACHEROUS BEAST!
UGH! UGH!

432
00:19:11,611 --> 00:19:12,545
AAH!

433
00:19:12,578 --> 00:19:14,478
- YOUR FEARS OF THE SPIDER HEADS
ARE NOW OVER.

434
00:19:14,511 --> 00:19:18,411
ONCE I'VE CONSUMED YOU,
YOU WILL BECOME PART OF ME!

435
00:19:18,445 --> 00:19:19,711
- FORGIVE ME, FATHER.

436
00:19:19,745 --> 00:19:23,645
I SHOULD NEVER HAVE
TRUSTED THIS MONSTER.

437
00:19:27,178 --> 00:19:31,111
- YOU'RE PRETTY DETERMINED,
FOR A HUMAN, THAT IS.

438
00:19:31,145 --> 00:19:32,478
- YOU'RE ALIVE?

439
00:19:32,511 --> 00:19:34,445
- INUYASHA!

440
00:19:34,478 --> 00:19:36,845
[CACKLES]

441
00:19:36,878 --> 00:19:37,978
INUYASHA!

442
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:39,678
- LOOK! THE SUN IS RISING!

443
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:40,545
- HUH?

444
00:19:40,578 --> 00:19:43,345
- YOU'RE A FINE
HUMAN SPECIMEN.

445
00:19:43,378 --> 00:19:46,345
- DON'T BE SO SURE ABOUT THAT.

446
00:19:49,845 --> 00:19:51,545
- YOU'RE BEGINNING
TO TRANSFORM,

447
00:19:51,578 --> 00:19:55,178
BUT I SHALL DEVOUR YOU
BEFOREHAND!

448
00:19:58,045 --> 00:20:00,011
- IF THERE'S ONE THING
I CAN'T STAND,

449
00:20:00,045 --> 00:20:01,811
IT'S AN ARROGANT SPIDER
THAT DOESN'T KNOW

450
00:20:01,845 --> 00:20:04,678
WHEN TO KEEP ITS HANDS OFF!

451
00:20:06,278 --> 00:20:09,678
THE MOONLESS NIGHT
HAS COME TO AN END!

452
00:20:11,478 --> 00:20:14,511
- THE AAH! SWORD'S
REGAINED ITS POWER!

453
00:20:14,545 --> 00:20:16,878
- YOU GOT IT, SPIDER HEAD!

454
00:20:16,911 --> 00:20:18,678
AAH!

455
00:20:33,178 --> 00:20:33,878
[CLANG]

456
00:20:33,911 --> 00:20:36,411
- THE SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL!

457
00:20:36,445 --> 00:20:39,878
THEY FUSED TOGETHER
INSIDE THE DEMON'S BODY!

458
00:20:39,911 --> 00:20:42,178
- IS THAT ALL
WE HAVE SO FAR?

459
00:20:42,211 --> 00:20:44,311
I THOUGHT WE HAD A LOT MORE.

460
00:20:44,345 --> 00:20:47,811
- HEY, IT'S ENOUGH
TO IMPRESS THIS GIRL.

461
00:20:50,278 --> 00:20:51,945
- THIS IS FAR ENOUGH.

462
00:20:51,978 --> 00:20:53,245
THE VILLAGE IS CLOSE BY.

463
00:20:53,278 --> 00:20:54,811
- OK.
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

464
00:20:54,845 --> 00:20:57,578
- OH, AND, INUYASHA,
I APPRECIATE YOUR HELP.

465
00:20:57,611 --> 00:21:01,311
I'LL TRY TO REMEMBER THAT
SOME DEMONS AREN'T ALL BAD.

466
00:21:01,345 --> 00:21:02,478
NOT MANY, BUT SOME.

467
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:04,278
- DON'T KID YOURSELF,
NAZUNA.

468
00:21:04,311 --> 00:21:07,078
ALL DEMONS ARE BAD.
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

469
00:21:07,111 --> 00:21:08,478
- I WON'T FORGET YOU!

470
00:21:08,511 --> 00:21:12,111
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE
IN MY PRAYERS, INUYASHA!

471
00:21:13,445 --> 00:21:16,611
- HUH.
WHATEVER.

472
00:21:18,978 --> 00:21:22,111
- HE SEEMS LIKE HIS OLD SELF.

473
00:21:24,845 --> 00:21:28,978
- KAGOME...YOU SMELL
KIND OF NICE.

474
00:21:29,011 --> 00:21:32,045
- DID HE ACTUALLY SAY THAT,
OR DID I HEAR WRONG?

475
00:21:32,078 --> 00:21:36,245
HIS BODY IS TRANSFORMED, BUT
WHAT ABOUT HIS FEELINGS FOR ME?

476
00:21:36,278 --> 00:21:37,945
SHOULD I ASK HIM?

477
00:21:37,978 --> 00:21:40,645
- HUH? ARE YOU GOING
TO KEEP STARING AT ME?

478
00:21:40,678 --> 00:21:41,911
BECAUSE IT'S TICKING ME OFF.

479
00:21:41,945 --> 00:21:43,945
IF YOU'VE GOT SOMETHING
TO SAY, SAY IT!

480
00:21:43,978 --> 00:21:47,445
- THEN AGAIN, SOME THINGS
ARE BETTER LEFT UNSAID.

481
00:21:47,478 --> 00:21:48,378
[MOANING]

482
00:21:48,411 --> 00:21:49,678
- ARE WE THERE YET?

483
00:21:49,711 --> 00:21:51,811
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE PULL OVER
FOR A SHORT REST?

484
00:21:51,845 --> 00:21:55,545
- YEAH, SURE, AS SOON AS YOU
GET OVER YOUR SEASICKNESS.

485
00:21:55,578 --> 00:21:58,278
- HEY, INUYASHA?
- HUH?

486
00:21:58,311 --> 00:21:59,711
[SHIPPO THROWS UP]
OH!

487
00:22:09,877 --> 00:22:12,444
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

488
00:23:37,851 --> 00:23:41,151
- IN A BATTLE FOR THE SACRED
JEWEL 50 YEARS AGO,

489
00:23:41,185 --> 00:23:44,885
INUYASHA WAS BOUND TO A TREE
BY KIKYO'S ARROW.

490
00:23:44,918 --> 00:23:46,151
KIKYO, KAEDE'S SISTER,

491
00:23:46,185 --> 00:23:48,018
WAS FATALLY INJURED
IN THE CONFRONTATION.

492
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:52,385
WE RETURNED FROM OUR JOURNEY
TO FIND KIKYO'S GRAVE SITE
DESECRATED!

493
00:23:52,418 --> 00:23:55,418
WHO WAS IT THAT ROBBED
THE GRAVE, AND WHY?

494
00:23:55,451 --> 00:23:59,585
SOMETHING TELLS ME THERE'S
GOING TO BE SERIOUS TROUBLE!

495
00:23:59,985 --> 00:24:03,385
NEXT TIME,
"KIKYO'S STOLEN ASHES."

496
00:24:03,418 --> 00:24:04,418
SEE YOU SOON!

